### Black-box test cases
# Test Design (Black Box Testing)

## Overview
This document covers the **Black Box Testing** for the module, including **Equivalence Partitioning (EP)** and **Boundary Value Analysis (BVA)** approaches. The test data includes specific values like the last four digits of your student ID (2061) and the corresponding expected results.

---

## **Module 1: `calculate_lucky_number` (Birthday-based lucky number calculation)**

### **Equivalence Partitioning (EP)**

| **Sr.** | **Boundary Value** | **Test Data**                             | **Expected Output**                             |
|---------|--------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| 1       | Valid input (valid date) | `03-05-1995`                            | Lucky Number: `9`                               |
| 2       | Invalid date format    | `32-13-2024`                            | `ValueError: Invalid date format or non-existent date.`  |
| 3       | Edge case (single digit day) | `01-01-2000`                            | Lucky Number: `3`                               |
| 4       | Edge case (multi-digit year) | `15-09-1987`                            | Lucky Number: `6`                               |
| 5       | Master number (11)    | `11-11-1985`                             | Lucky Number: `11`                              |
| 6       | Master number (22)    | `22-02-1982`                             | Lucky Number: `22`                              |
| 7       | Invalid date, non-existent month | `15-13-1998`                         | `ValueError: Invalid date format or non-existent date.` |

### **Boundary Value Analysis (BVA)**

| **Sr.** | **Boundary Value** | **Test Data**                             | **Expected Output**                             |
|---------|--------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| 1       | Near valid boundary (date close to range) | `31-12-1999`                            | Lucky Number: `7`                               |
| 2       | Near invalid boundary (invalid date) | `29-02-2024`                            | Lucky Number: `5`                               |

---

## **Module 2: `determine_lucky_animal` (Determine the lucky animal based on lucky number)**

### **Equivalence Partitioning (EP)**

| **Sr.** | **Boundary Value** | **Test Data**                             | **Expected Output**                             |
|---------|--------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| 1       | Valid input (lucky number within range) | `6`                                      | Lucky Animal: `Deer`                            |
| 2       | Boundary value (master number) | `11`                                     | Lucky Animal: `Dolphin`                         |
| 3       | Invalid input (lucky number out of range) | `35`                                     | Lucky Animal: `Unknown`                         |
| 4       | Edge case (minimum valid number) | `1`                                       | Lucky Animal: `Parrot`                          |

### **Boundary Value Analysis (BVA)**

| **Sr.** | **Boundary Value** | **Test Data**                             | **Expected Output**                             |
|---------|--------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| 1       | Boundary value (maximum valid number) | `33`                                     | Lucky Animal: `Turtle`                          |
| 2       | Boundary for unknown input | `0`                                      | Lucky Animal: `Unknown`                         |

