## **Module 3: `find_generation` (Determine the generation based on birth year)**

### **Equivalence Partitioning (EP)**

| **Sr.** | **Boundary Value** | **Test Data**                             | **Expected Output**                             |
|---------|--------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| 1       | Valid generation (Baby Boomers) | `15-07-1960`                            | Generation: `Baby Boomers`                      |
| 2       | Valid generation (Millennials)  | `22-03-1995`                            | Generation: `Millennials`                       |
| 3       | Valid generation (Generation Z) | `25-12-2005`                            | Generation: `Generation Z`                      |
| 4       | Invalid generation (before 1900) | `25-12-1899`                            | Generation: `Unknown Generation`                |
| 5       | Invalid generation (after 2025) | `10-05-2030`                            | Generation: `Unknown Generation`                |

### **Boundary Value Analysis (BVA)**

| **Sr.** | **Boundary Value** | **Test Data**                             | **Expected Output**                             |
|---------|--------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| 1       | Edge boundary (Baby Boomers) | `01-01-1946`                            | Generation: `Baby Boomers`                      |
| 2       | Edge boundary (Generation Alpha) | `01-01-2010`                            | Generation: `Generation Alpha`                  |

---

## **Module 4: `compare_birthdays` (Compare lucky numbers and animals of two birthdays)**

### **Equivalence Partitioning (EP)**

| **Sr.** | **Boundary Value** | **Test Data**                             | **Expected Output**                             |
|---------|--------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| 1       | Same lucky numbers and animals | `03-05-1995`, `03-05-1995`                | Lucky Numbers: Same, Lucky Animals: Same       |
| 2       | Different lucky numbers and animals | `15-09-1987`, `25-12-1983`                | Lucky Numbers: Different, Lucky Animals: Different |
| 3       | Invalid date format in one of the inputs | `03-05-1995`, `32-13-2024`                | `ValueError: One or both dates are in an invalid format.` |

### **Boundary Value Analysis (BVA)**

| **Sr.** | **Boundary Value** | **Test Data**                             | **Expected Output**                             |
|---------|--------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| 1       | Compare valid boundary dates | `01-01-1990`, `01-01-1991`                | Lucky Numbers: Different, Lucky Animals: Different |
| 2       | Compare dates near boundary values | `31-12-1999`, `01-01-2000`                | Lucky Numbers: Different, Lucky Animals: Different |

